description: For sale: $499,500. This is a to be built home by award winning Thorson Homes, a builder known for their attention to detail and quality built homes for over 40 years. There is no home on the property currently. Wonderful new Eagan development with this and 6 other walk out lots available to build on and an additional neighborhood to select from. This 2 story home will feature 4 bedrooms (on one level), 3 bathrooms, upper level laundry room and high end finishes including enameled trim, quartz counter tops, stainless steel appliances and 3 car garage on a cul de sac. In Eagan school district - Red Pine Elementary, Dakota Middle School & Eagan High School. Come help design your dream home and let us be the first to welcome you home! Come see our model home in the Summerbrooke neighborhood in Eagan and start planning your home. 6 other walk out lots available to build on in this development as well as another development nearby.

For sale: $719,900. Welcome to Avid Builders model in Summerbrooke Place. This is a great opportunity to purchase finished, new construction with endless upgrades. This carefully crafted home features white enameled wainscoting throughout the first floor. Solid wood, engineered flooring has the elegance of wood with the toughness of a pre-finished floor. The great room gas fireplace is finished with floor to ceiling stone. Quartz counter-tops are easy to care for and set off the ceramic tile backsplash, upgraded appliances and unique door pulls. The main floor office with upgraded carpet and a wall of floor to ceiling wainscoting is right next to the front door. There are 4 bedrooms up, a master suite with free-standing tub, walk in tile shower and wall papered accent wall. The finished basement family room offers a second place for recreation and future opportunity to finish 2 more bedrooms and a bath. Move-In ready!

description:
Recently sold: $168,000. Warm, inviting and accessible.  Not only is it on the first floor, but it's near all the amenities of Eagan.  You feel tucked away in your own quiet haven, but every store you need is within 1.5 miles of your front door.  

Neighborhood Description

The association of homes is tucked away below a main road and adjacent to a golf course.  It has beautiful views while having significantly reduced street noise.
